{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599086","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599086"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:49:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:49:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15525"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15525","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15525"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.16,0.71,0.02,0.04,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8216"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61732"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8216","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8216"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15525"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47178"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19874"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19876"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61732","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/61732"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAirway remodeling is a key pathological feature of chronic asthma that involves structural changes to the bronchial walls.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following changes occurs in chronic asthma?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Smooth muscle atrophy","Subepithelial collagen deposition","Decreased mucus production","Epithelial cell hyperplasia reduction","Basement membrane thinning"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn chronic asthma, several structural changes occur in the airways:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESmooth muscle atrophy\u003C/strong\u003E does not occur - instead there is smooth muscle hypertrophy and hyperplasia\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubepithelial collagen deposition\u003C/strong\u003E is a characteristic finding, leading to thickening of the basement membrane\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased mucus production\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - there is increased mucus production due to goblet cell hyperplasia\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEpithelial cell hyperplasia reduction\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - epithelial cell hyperplasia increases\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBasement membrane thinning\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - the basement membrane becomes thickened\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese changes contribute to airway hyperresponsiveness and chronic narrowing of the airways.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Airway remodeling in asthma includes subepithelial fibrosis, smooth muscle hypertrophy, and mucus gland hyperplasia","Chronic inflammation in asthma leads to structural changes in the bronchial walls"],"references":["Kudo M, Ishigatsubo Y, Aoki I. Pathology of asthma. Front Microbiol. 2013 Sep 10;4:263. doi: 10.3389/fmicb.2013.00263. PMID: 24032029; PMCID: PMC3768124.","Yeh SY, Schwartzstein R. Asthma: Pathophysiology and Diagnosis. Asthma, Health and Society. 2009 Jun 8:19\u201342. doi: 10.1007/978-0-387-78285-0_2. PMCID: PMC7176227.","Sinyor B, Concepcion Perez L. Pathophysiology Of Asthma. [Updated 2023 Jun 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK551579/","Mason, R. J., Broaddus, V. C., Martin, T. R., King, T. E., Schraufnagel, D., Murray, J. F., \